  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Process Improvement Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>Location:</strong> Loyang, Singapore  <strong>Industry:</strong> Aviation / Aerospace</p><p>Take the lead in <strong>shaping operational excellence</strong> at a leading Singapore-based Aerospace MRO operator. As Continuous Improvement Manager, you will partner directly with the General Manager to drive <strong>Lean, Six Sigma, and digital transformation initiatives</strong>, improving quality, turnaround time, cost efficiency, and safety across Part 145 maintenance operations.</p><p>My client is  looking for a <strong>hands-on, strategic leader</strong> who thrives in complex, safety-critical environments and can turn process improvement into measurable business results.</p><p><strong>What You’ll Do:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Lead <strong>Lean & Six Sigma programs</strong> to boost shop-floor performance and operational KPIs</p></li><li><p>Partner with GM to deliver <strong>data-driven, high-impact decisions</strong></p></li><li><p>Drive local execution of <strong>global Customer Support & transformation initiatives</strong></p></li><li><p>Mentor teams and embed a <strong>sustainable culture of continuous improvement</strong></p></li><li><p>Track, analyze, and report <strong>operational performance and project benefits</strong></p></li></ul><p><strong>What You Bring:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Lean or Six Sigma Black Belt (preferred) with <strong>hands-on MRO experience</strong></p></li><li><p>5+ years in <strong>Aerospace/Aviation MRO</strong>, ideally Part 145</p></li><li><p>Deep understanding of <strong>MRO workflows, safety, and regulatory compliance</strong></p></li><li><p>Proven ability to <strong>lead cross-functional projects</strong> and manage change</p></li><li><p>Strong analytical, project management, and stakeholder engagement skills</p></li></ul><p><strong>Why Join My Client:</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>High-visibility, strategic role</strong> in a leading MRO operation</p></li><li><p>Directly <strong>impact operational excellence</strong> and customer satisfaction</p></li><li><p>Exposure to <strong>global aerospace programs</strong> and digital transformation initiatives</p></li><li><p>Opportunity to <strong>shape a culture of continuous improvement</strong> in a dynamic environment</p></li></ul><p><strong>Elevate your career in aerospace operational excellence – apply now.</strong></p>",
